b7=A.ai("Project:",A.a4(a6,a6,a6,a6,a6,B.r),a6,a6)
b5=A.ai("Development of a sound controlled video game to teach music concepts,  support creative expression and spark musical interactions between the community of young music learners.\n                    ",A.a4(a6,a6,a6,a6,a6,a6),a6,a6)
r=A.ai("Challenges:",A.a4(a6,a6,a6,a6,a6,B.r),a6,a6)
q=A.ai("Lack of feedback and social connection are detrimental for the perseverance of music students that rehearse at home. Music video games based on gamification rules can engage students in practice and connect them with their peers. Although, music video games require either replacing the instrument for a controller, which hinders didactic capacity of the game, or physically connecting the instrument to the computer which negatively impacts interaction and range of freedom and creativity.\n                    ",A.a4(a6,a6,a6,a6,a6,a6),a6,a6)
p=A.ai("Process:",A.a4(a6,a6,a6,a6,a6,B.r),a6,a6)
o=A.ai("The challenge was into four development milestones. Each milestone will produce a deliverable that can be presented as a finished product and be used as a base for the next iteration of development. \n                    ",A.a4(a6,a6,a6,a6,a6,a6),a6,a6)
n=A.ai("Natural interaction:",A.a4(a6,a6,B.Z,a6,a6,a6),a6,a6)
m=A.ai("A realtime digital signal processing algorithm was developed and implemented to transform the sound of a violin into game inputs (amplitude and frequency of the dominant harmonics) that still reflected the musical expression they represent. . The amplitude of the signal was used to trigger the movement of the character, while the frequency determined the direction of the movement. That way the music students need only play their violin naturally to interact with the game. (The project was built for pc, mac, android, google cardboard in android and the web).\n                    ",A.a4(a6,a6,a6,a6,a6,a6),a6,a6)
l=A.ai("Teaching a music concept:",A.a4(a6,a6,B.Z,a6,a6,a6),a6,a6)
k=A.ai("A configurable metronome was implemented to keep track of the beat of the background music at each level of the game. The metronome implemented a timer which kept track of the elapsed time since the last tick. When a new note is detected, comparing the period between ticks with the time since the last tick can tell us if the player was \u2018on time\u2019 or how far off he was.\n                    ",A.a4(a6,a6,a6,a6,a6,a6),a6,a6)
j=A.ai("Creative freedom:",A.a4(a6,a6,B.Z,a6,a6,a6),a6,a6)
i=A.ai("Sampling the amplitude and frequency of the player performance over time generates two curves that roughly describe the improvisation. The patterns of interaction between these curves can hint at common techniques such as arpeggio, crescendo, legato, staccato, accents, etc, which can trigger different game interactions during the improvisation. These \u2018musical descriptors\u2019 were used to distinctly alter the growth pattern of a tree (shape, size and color), which was shaped during the player\u2019s improvisation and served as a visual expression of his unique ability and personality. \n                    ",A.a4(a6,a6,a6,a6,a6,a6),a6,a6)
